 MBOMBELA – Lowvelders were pummeled by a swift, but heavy hailstorm on Tuesday evening with damage to property reported across Mbombela. Residents expressed their shock and in some instances awe, at the size and severity of the hailstorm accompanied by spectacular lightning and thunder throughout the evening. Read more: Man confirmed dead after storm wreaks havoc in Nkomazi Lowvelders can expect more rainfall today and tomorrow with a 30 per cent rainfall probability and a maximum temperature of 16 degrees Celsius forecast for Thursday. Read more: More photos of hail and storm damage in Rocky Drift Do you have pictures or a video that you would like to share with us? Please send your pictures or videos to hancu@lowvelder.co.za